Code Book
========================================================

The run_analysis script uses the data in the "UCI HAR Dataset" to create the TidyData file with four columns: subject, activity, variable and average. 

The following is a description of each column:

#subject

This column contains the subject who performed the activity for each window sample. 
Integers, range from 1 to 30.

#activity

This column contains the activity the subject performed.

Characters, with one of the following values:
* laying
* sitting
* standing
* walking
* walking downstairs
* walking upstairs

#variable

This column contains the name of the measurement. Only contains mean and standard deviation measurements from orginal dataset. 

Characters, for example: "TimeBodyAcc_mean_X"

#average   

This column contains the mean of each measurement taken by subject and activity.

Numeric, range from -1 to 1.
